definition: (of a publisher) to send a manuscript off to the printer/(of a journalist) to send a dispatch
to send out/to show (one's feeling)/to issue/to develop/to make a bundle of money/classifier for gunshots (rounds)

sentences.english: At press time , there is still no news of the plane.
sentences.chinese: 截至发稿时，仍然没有这架飞机的消息。

sentences.english: People can sit down and read our handout.
sentences.chinese: 人们可以坐下来，慢慢读这些分发稿。

sentences.english: To press upon, the Pudong International Airport, flights and order was gradually restored.
sentences.chinese: 到记者发稿时止，浦东国际机场航班秩序也逐渐恢复。

sentences.english: By that time, sincere product has not yet response to customer.
sentences.chinese: 截止发稿，凡客诚品尚未给予回应。

sentences.english: Jingtian & Gongcheng did not respond to requests for comment by press time.
sentences.chinese: 截至发稿时间，竞天公诚为对置评请求作出回应。

sentences.english: When the journalist again failed to reply, the editor reluctantly publish the article as it had originally been written.
sentences.chinese: 记者还是没有回复，编辑出于无奈还是按原样发稿了。

sentences.english: Fangda Partners did not respond by press time.
sentences.chinese: 截至发稿，方达未作出回应。

sentences.english: As of press time reporter, Davao flood casualties have multiple versions.
sentences.chinese: 截至记者发稿时，达沃洪灾伤亡人数有多个版本。

sentences.english: At press time, Karp had received no response.
sentences.chinese: 直到发稿，卡普没有收到任何回应。

sentences.english: Discussions continued as The Economist went to press.
sentences.chinese: 截至《经济学人》发稿前，讨论仍在继续。

definition: (of a newspaper) to stop accepting incoming articles
to close/to stop/to put a stop to sth/cut-off point/stopping point/deadline
